Definition: concerned with principles of right and wrong or conforming to standards of behavior and character based on those principles
Example: moral sense; a moral scrutiny; a moral lesson; a moral quandary; moral convictions; a moral life
Synonyms: noun, attribute, morality, IMMORAL, CHASTE, GOOD, HONORABLE, RIGHTEOUS, VIRTUOUS, concerned, with, principles, of, right, and, wrong, or, conforming, to, standards, behavior, character, based, on, those, moral, sense, a, scrutiny, lesson, quandary, convictions, life
Category: adj.all
